				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$U_{3} \left({r_{ij},r_{ik}} \right) = \epsilon [\cos_{ijk} - \cos_{0}]^{2} \times \exp \left({\frac{\sigma}{{r_{ij} - a\sigma}}} \right) \times \exp \left({\frac{\sigma}{{r_{ik} - a\sigma}}} \right)$$\end{document}

In this work, we use the parameters A = 7.049556277, B  = 0.6022245584, p = 4, q = 0, cosθ0=13\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
